   [DDF-small]
   Judging Criteria
     __________________________________________________________________

   DDF proposals are judged by how well they answer the questions within
   the following categories:

   Innovation:
   How innovative is the proposed project?

   Risk:
   Is the proposed project High risk / high payoff? DDF funds are intended
       to be seed money to stimulate new ideas.

   Integrated Organizational Approach:
   Is the proposed project interdisciplinary, such that it crosses
       organization lines? Such as Science-Engineering, Internal-External,
       or Space-Earth Science.

   Goddard:

        Is the proposed project relevant to Goddard and it's mission?

        Will the proposed project help position GSFC for the future?

   If you are proposing a project that would be classified as and
          Educational or Outreach proposal please view the Judging
          Criteria that these proposals will be judged by.


